2000-02-07  Akim Demaille  <akim@epita.fr>

	* acgeneral.m4 (AC_CHECK_TYPE_INTERNAL): Instead of defining an
	unused pointer to the type $1, use
	if (($1 *) 0) return 0;
	to avoid warnings from the compiler.
	From Paul Eggert.

